Rating: 3
There were a few reviewers that said the risotto was bland. I took that as a warning and added a few extra ingredients. I also took and made the recipe for 2 instead of one and it came out perfect. After you add the rice to the pan put in a ¼ cup of dry white wine and let it soak in, then start adding the broth. I also added half of a small onion to the mix, finely chopped and 2 extra cloves of garlic. During the cooking process I added a couple pinches of sea salt to give it a little extra flavor. I would still recommend added the lemon zest at the end it adds a good touch to the risotto. All in all it was a good dish. I also did not add that much water to my broth. I left the bacon grease and in the pan which wasnt much if you can find lean bacon it works the best.

