Rating: 0
This recipe is written for one serving which I found strange. So for six servings or better you should make at least 2 cups of the Aborio Rice. I made three cups, used 6 slices of bacon, used an entire stick of salted butter, and about a cup or better of parmesan cheese. Also added some frozen corn too. As for the bland taste, bump it up by using FAR more garlic than this recipe calls for. I used garlic powder instead of real garlic and did it to taste. TOTALLY omitted any lemon because my kids wouldn't like that. Entire family loved it. It's a repeat!

